Graduate Student Resources


Welcome to the Department of Informatics Graduate Program resource microsite. The goal of this microsite is to provide easy access to information and resources that can support you in your studies. The site contains a robust FAQ with answers to all kinds of questions, so please start there with your questions. If you don’t find the answer you are looking for please reach out to your faculty advisor or to Katie Salen Tekinbas, Vice Chair of Graduate Affairs. You can also visit the Key Contacts for a list of people tasked with supporting graduate students—they are all here to help.


